node.text:
Answering lots of questions I’ve been receiving about my new weekly newsletters.
Link for this set- https://bit.ly/weeklynewsletters

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Maribel-Learning in Wonderland on September 02, 2021.

node.text: I shared my two page lesson plan layout the other day, but I’m also loving these one page layouts! I made sure to include the sticky note area on top still because I find that so useful. These include editable and black and white copies too! Link in profile: https://bit.ly/liwlessonplans

node.text:
Heads up to those of you who own my planner basics and planner essentials bundles!

Go re-download because I added a new resource to both of them yesterday! If you have been considering purchasing either bundle, make sure to use code BTSBONUS21 to grab them 25% off today!

PS I’m also getting a lot of questions about the planner I add my inserts to. I’m a huge fan of @the_happy_planner! I picked this one up at Walmart, but you can find them at any craft store too!

Link in profile for the basics bundle- http://bit.ly/plannerbasics

node.text:
🥳 New and on SALE!!!!🥳 I’ve received so many requests for lesson plan templates over the years! I’m so happy to have these done and ready to go for you!

One of my favorite parts is the sticky note area up on top. I always needed this on my lesson plans so I made sure to include that. Link in profile: https://bit.ly/liwlessonplans

node.text: These comprehension mini books are some of my favorite things to use in the classroom and FYI... the Spanish versions are coming soon! 🤩 Let me know if you want to be tagged when they are ready. 😊 Link in profile- http://bit.ly/minicomprehensionbooks

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Maribel-Learning in Wonderland on August 28, 2021 tagging @walmart, and @crayola. May be an image of cosmetics.

node.text: These @crayola Clicks are just so beautiful!! I’m using them just about every day. I got the 20 pack from @walmart and it includes all the colors 😍 I’d say these are perfect for grading and writing notes on student papers. I wouldn’t suggest these for anchor charts because they write on the thinner side. I’d compare them to Fine Point Sharpies in terms of the tip size.

node.text:
Have you heard about @vooks new buy one, give 35 deal? #ad When a teacher purchases a yearlong subscription, every student gets an account to access from home! 🙌🏽

Their book selections are so amazing! Have you checked out this one from Shannon Olsen AKA @lifebetweensummers? It's perfect for the beginning of the year! 

Vooks also has free resources for some of their most popular titles.

Link in profile to check out this educator exclusive offer!
#vooks #betterscreentime #vookspartner #backtoschool

I wish I had this digital documentation/parent communication log LONG ago!

I don’t know how many times I forgot to document something because I didn’t have my log on me. With it being saved in Google Sheets, it can now be pulled up anywhere on any device for documentation on the go! 🙌🏽

This resource includes print and digital versions for you to use. Link in profile: https://bit.ly/schoolcommunicationlog

node.text:
In Focus✨ This bulletin board was a game changer once we started using it. It helped my students and kept me on track throughout our reading block.

The headings are editable so you can customize them for other subjects.

The posters can be used two ways: 
1. You can leave them blank and hand write your content with dry erase markers each day. 
2. You can type in your content from your curriculum.

I went with option 2 so that I could reuse the cards from year to year. Saved me so much time! 🙌🏽

Link in bio- http://bit.ly/editablefocuswall

node.text:
Getting lots of questions about this so I’m here to share all the answers for you.

FAQs:
1. Are these editable?
Yes, both the word chart and bookmark options include editable and pre-made copies.

2. Do I have to print on labels? 
No, you can print on regular paper and glue them into your students’ notebooks.

3. Is this just for early grades?
You can use the editable version to add any sight word list for any grade.

4. Can I print in black and white?
The word chart has a black and white copy. The bookmark doesn’t, but I can add it if someone needs it.

5. Where can I find the writer’s workshop label from the video?
I linked it in my Notebook Labels highlight.

6. What printer do you use? I have an HP that I love. I linked it in my Amazon highlights for you.

7. Where can I find the half sheet labels you used? I get mine from Amazon. I also linked them in my Notebook Labels highlight for you.

Hope that answers any questions you may have. ❤️

If you are looking for this sight word chart, the link is in my profile 😊
